data.description: Spectacular large brick home conveniently located in a peaceful rural setting near Nitchkey field.   From the time you step in the ceramic tiled foyer until you finish browsing  the home you will be greeted with surprise after surprise at the spaciousness of this solid 1960's beauty.   Head straight to the kitchen to see the beautifully updated cabinets, quartz counters and stainless steel appliances with tile flooring.   There is a generous living room with hardwood floors and lots of natural light.  The dining room  has built in shelving to beautifully display your treasures. Conveniently located on this first level is an office with more built in shelving and a half bath providing the opportunity for an additional first floor bedroom. This property has 3 large bedrooms that complement the oversized primary suite. This primary suite boasts a large bathroom,  a walk in closet, a laundry room and a 10x23 sitting room that has a balcony leading to the lower patio.   Let's head downstairs to the finished lower level that has a wood burning fireplace and patio doors to a large level half acre plus lot.  Need a lot of storage space?  Look no more...approximately 500 sq. feet of the lower level is for storage... so store away!!  You can enjoy the best of both worlds with the potential of outdoor living during the warmer weather and indoor entertaining with plenty of room to socialize all year round. Most of the 2nd floor and all of the main level have been painted recently.   The rear patio area and the oversized two car garage add to the appeal of this home as well as the convenience of nearby schools, shopping and close proximity to the Maryland line.  This deep cleaned home is ready for you to make it your own.  Hurry and schedule your showing!!
